uccessful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Trye was born about 1435, in Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom as the son of John Trye. He married Isabel Berkeley about 1465, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 6 December 1497, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 63, and was buried in Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1435–6 December 1497":"umbes 1435–6. detsember 1497","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1442–1485":"1442–1485","1437–1498":"1437–1498","1468–1524":"1468–1524","1414–Male":"1414–Surnud","1437":"1437","1414":"1414","1524":"1524","1468":"1468","1435":"1435","Abt 1465":"umbes 1465","1498":"1498","1442":"1442","1497":"1497","1485":"1485","Abt 1435":"umbes 1435","6 December 1497":"6. detsember 1497","Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, England":"Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hardwicke and Redwick, Gloucester, England":"Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hardwicke, Stroud District, Gloucestershire, England":"Hardwicke, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1435–6 December 1497":"noin 1435–6. joulukuuta 1497","1435–1497":"1435–1497","1442–1485":"1442–1485","1437–1498":"1437–1498","1468–1524":"1468–1524","1414–Male"